the India-Pakistan War of 1947. This war took a supreme toll on the Kashmiris as they suffered the most catastrophic atrocities.

The Kashmir issue became an international conflict between India and Pakistan era. People, who were not even born in 1947, have to face the blame and the burden of what their forefathers did over the passage of years.

As the Kashmiris are caught in the midst of two independent nations, India and Pakistan, they have to survive and look forward to a better future, away from the brutal wars and tyrannical suppression.

The Kashmiri youngsters have witnessed many wars around them, which have taken their loved once. The best solution to Kashmir is an independent Kashmir, because, it would be accepted worldwide, and the Kashmiris would be able to get their natural rights, which they longer have.

The present situation is intolerable for the people of Kashmir. The better solution is a common Kashmiri front to level the field, so that the Kashmiris would have better opportunities to act independently on behalf of Kashmir.

Anything that has happened, no matter how evil it was done, has not directly affected every person in India. The only way to solve the issue is through a referendum.

Before any peace talks, Kashmiris must be let know of their legal rights as to what, when and how they can act.
